4.3 Execution Flow (Real example)
Scenario: Incident happens

Payments API failing.

Instead of:

❌ “Search docs → copy commands → SSH → pray”

They use:

InfoGrid:
Dashboard → payments → Rollback → Click

Behind the scenes:
Step-by-step
1️⃣ User clicks action

"Rollback payments"

2️⃣ InfoGrid validates

permissions

environment

dependencies

safety checks

3️⃣ Selects execution method

GitHub Actions

Kubernetes job

SSH runner

Self-hosted runner

Argo Workflow

4️⃣ Executes

Runs:

helm rollback payments

5️⃣ Logs results

success/failure

output

audit trail

6️⃣ Updates knowledge graph

State now updated to previous version

Result

Client sees:

✅ Rollback complete
✅ Logs attached
✅ Incident resolved
